        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2016-06-07 23:05:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nAndreas could this replace the need for the LU-684 work?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "c286ac14270d4508a655dd00c070f49eb2c10fd2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2016-06-07 23:31:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nNo, because this doesn't permanently block/drop writes to the device, only temporarily while the IO is flushed and the journal committed.  If the device was permanently frozen, then all the MDS/OSS threads would be blocked and potentially client threads would become blocked when their max_rpcs_in_flight limit was reached.  Many of the recovery tests would not work properly because they expect a reply from the server before the server is restarted.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
